27/07/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Wrapping up a two-day visit to Zagreb on Tuesday (26 July), NATO's Supreme Allied Commander Europe, General James L. 
Jones, expressed satisfaction with his talks with Croatian leaders, saying the meetings were useful in the context of the situation in the Balkans and future collaboration. 
He reiterated support for Croatia's NATO bid, noting that the issue of membership would be decided at a political level. 
The general thanked Zagreb for its contribution to operations in Afghanistan and stressed that increased co-operation is crucial to bringing the Croatian military into line with NATO standards. 
(HRT, HINA - 27/07/05)
